dataIdInfo.idPurp: Administrative boundary lines for level 0-3. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent. DISCLAIMER: Syria Admin Levels 4 and 5 are not included in this dataset due to nesting issues

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was created by ITOS by converting the Admin 3 layer, which was downloaded from HDX, to lines. The lines were created after all processing on the Admin 3 layer had been completed by ITOS.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in. For example, if a boundary line is shared between an Admin 2 unit and an Admin 3 unit, it is attributed with an 'AdminLevel' value of "2".
